The conditional if (1) is a constant true test that is evaluated at runtime but has no effect on behaviour — the body always executes. The evaluation/branch operation is therefore redundant: removing the surrounding if (1) (leaving the body) would not change program behaviour. This constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. A fix is to remove the if (1) wrapper (or use a legitimate mechanism such as (void)res to suppress warnings) so no executed-but-redundant operation remains.
